## Section 23: Loading States & Skeletons

### 23.1 Loading State Hierarchy

**Principles**:
1. **Skeleton screens** for predictable layouts
2. **Spinners** for indeterminate operations
3. **Progress bars** for tracked operations
4. **Optimistic updates** for instant feedback

### 23.2 Skeleton Loader Pattern

```tsx
const TransactionSkeleton = () => (
  <div className="animate-pulse space-y-4">
    {[1, 2, 3, 4, 5].map((i) => (
      <div key={i} className="flex items-center justify-between p-4 bg-white/5 rounded-xl">
        <div className="flex items-center space-x-4">
          <div className="w-10 h-10 bg-white/10 rounded-full" />
          <div className="space-y-2">
            <div className="h-4 w-32 bg-white/10 rounded" />
            <div className="h-3 w-24 bg-white/10 rounded" />
          </div>
        </div>
        <div className="h-6 w-20 bg-white/10 rounded" />
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>
);

const TransactionsList = () => {
  const { data, loading } = useTransactions();

  if (loading) return <TransactionSkeleton />;

  return data.map(txn => <TransactionRow key={txn.id} {...txn} />);
};
```

### 23.3 Button Loading States

```tsx
// Already implemented in Button component (Section 9)
<Button variant="primary" isLoading={true}>
  Processing...
</Button>

// Renders as:
<button className="...">
  <Loader className="h-4 w-4 animate-spin mr-2" />
  <span>Processing...</span>
</button>
```

### 23.4 Progressive Loading Pattern

```tsx
const DashboardPage = () => {
  const [statsLoaded, setStatsLoaded] = useState(false);
  const [chartsLoaded, setChartsLoaded] = useState(false);
  const [transactionsLoaded, setTransactionsLoaded] = useState(false);

  useEffect(() => {
    // Load critical data first
    loadStats().then(() => setStatsLoaded(true));

    // Then load secondary data
    loadCharts().then(() => setChartsLoaded(true));

    // Finally load heavy data
    loadTransactions().then(() => setTransactionsLoaded(true));
  }, []);

  return (
    <div>
      {/* Critical stats load first */}
      {statsLoaded ? <StatsGrid /> : <StatsSkeleton />}

      {/* Charts load second */}
      {chartsLoaded ? <RevenueChart /> : <ChartSkeleton />}

      {/* Heavy table loads last */}
      {transactionsLoaded ? <TransactionsTable /> : <TableSkeleton />}
    </div>
  );
};
```

